article.headline: Loyola, Md. 75, Rider 61
article.story: LAWRENCEVILLE, N.J. -- Jamal Barney scored a game-high 28 points to lead Loyola to a 75-61 win over Rider Friday night. Loyola (11-12, 6-5 MAAC) led by one at halftime, 32-31. The Greyhounds outscored Rider 18-6 to start the second half, keyed by eight points from Bret Harvey, to take a 50-37 lead. Rider (11-9, 6-4) then went on a 17-7 run to cut the lead to 57-54 with 5:04 to play, but the Broncs could get no closer. Ryan Thompson and Mike Ringgold both had 13 points to lead Rider. Harvey wound up with 18 points for Loyola, and Jawaan Wright pulled down a game-high 11 rebounds.
